video_title: Small margin of Democrat to Republican early-voters 'not looking good for Biden'
video_description:
If there is a surge of republican votes on election day, as CBS, a mainstream American media is predicting, Donald Trump will be returned to presidency, according to Sky News host Paul Murray. 

 “The assumption has always been that Democrats are voting early and they are voting by a margin of 2-1,” Mr Murray said.

“But, if that’s the case, it means on election day, republicans vote 2-1, so you’ve got to have massive margins going into election day."

Mr Murray showed a recently released CBS poll which revealed 66 per cent of Democrats had already voted, while 69 per cent of Republicans were planning to vote on election day.

“Our theory is holding up,” he said. 

“The Biden vote should be big margins in the places he needs to win, but if there is a Trump surge, CBS, lefty, mainstream media America is predicting, that if this is true, Donald Trump is returned to the presidency.

“He’d have 279 electoral college votes.

“If Joe Biden is so far ahead in the opinion polls, and he’s so far ahead in terms of those who identify themselves as Democrats to have voted already for him, the margins need to be big.”

Mr Murray gave an in-depth analysis of pre-polling and the early-vote in key states across the US ahead of the election.

video_title: Dem PA LG: Trump At “Level Of Barnstorming That I Can’t Recall Another Candidate Has Done Before”
Trump and Biden face off in final US presidential debate - highlights
video_description:
Catch up on the highlights of the final US presidential debate between Donald Trump and Joe Biden.

Joe Biden has renewed his attack on President Donald Trump's handling of the coronavirus pandemic ahead of the presidential election on 3 November.

The Democratic candidate told the debate in Nashville, Tennessee: "Anyone who's responsible for that many deaths should not remain president of the United States of America.

"He says we're, you know, learning to live with it. People are learning to die with it."

Mr Trump responded by saying: "We're rounding the corner. It's going away," adding that "we can't close up our nation or we won't have one".

video_title: Nebraska Trump rally turn out of  29,000 people was a 'wake-up moment for the media'
video_description:
Sky News US political commentator Joe Hockey says when 29,000 people turned up for a Trump rally in Nebraska the other day, it was a wake-up moment for the media.
 
“It is extraordinary, it’s almost like a cult movement and he’s like a cult leader and people are coming out in vast numbers,” Mr Hockey said. 

Mr Hockey said Trump went to five cities across the country on Sunday, and people in Florida were queued up waiting for his arrival from 7am right through until beyond 11:30pm. 

“It is building a momentum, there’s no doubt about that,” he said.

“He is hungry and it shows. He really wants people votes and that’s given him momentum in the last 48 hours.

“It’s really hard to read the impact of that momentum on the electoral votes.”

video_title: Small margin of Democrat to Republican early-voters 'not looking good for Biden'
video_description:
If there is a surge of republican votes on election day, as CBS, a mainstream American media is predicting, Donald Trump will be returned to presidency, according to Sky News host Paul Murray. 

 “The assumption has always been that Democrats are voting early and they are voting by a margin of 2-1,” Mr Murray said.

“But, if that’s the case, it means on election day, republicans vote 2-1, so you’ve got to have massive margins going into election day."

Mr Murray showed a recently released CBS poll which revealed 66 per cent of Democrats had already voted, while 69 per cent of Republicans were planning to vote on election day.

“Our theory is holding up,” he said. 

“The Biden vote should be big margins in the places he needs to win, but if there is a Trump surge, CBS, lefty, mainstream media America is predicting, that if this is true, Donald Trump is returned to the presidency.

“He’d have 279 electoral college votes.

“If Joe Biden is so far ahead in the opinion polls, and he’s so far ahead in terms of those who identify themselves as Democrats to have voted already for him, the margins need to be big.”

Mr Murray gave an in-depth analysis of pre-polling and the early-vote in key states across the US ahead of the election.

video_title: Trump and Biden face off in final US presidential debate - highlights
video_description:
Catch up on the highlights of the final US presidential debate between Donald Trump and Joe Biden.

Joe Biden has renewed his attack on President Donald Trump's handling of the coronavirus pandemic ahead of the presidential election on 3 November.

The Democratic candidate told the debate in Nashville, Tennessee: "Anyone who's responsible for that many deaths should not remain president of the United States of America.

"He says we're, you know, learning to live with it. People are learning to die with it."

Mr Trump responded by saying: "We're rounding the corner. It's going away," adding that "we can't close up our nation or we won't have one".

video_title: Biden can't negotiate with China because he’s been ‘bought’ by Beijing: Trump
video_description:
President Trump has accused Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden of being a “corrupt politician bought and paid for by China” during a rally at Charlotte Douglas International Airport in North Carolina.

“How can you have a guy whose son walks out with a billion and a half dollars to manage … whose son asked for $10 million dollars a year for introductory purposes”.

Speaking of Mr Biden’s alleged links to Hunter Biden’s Chinese dealings, the president asked how the Democratic candidate was "supposed to be negotiating with China” given the compromising circumstances.

He claimed the communist nation must be hoping he doesn’t return to the White House, pointing out his administration had “taken in tens of billions of dollars a year, for the first time ever, from China”.

The Biden campaign has strenuously denied their candidate was involved in any overseas business dealings with China.

video_title: BLM riots are ‘perfectly scripted’ for Trump to push law and order
video_description:
Documentary film maker Ami Horowitz says the major battleground states in the US election seem to be trending tighter and tighter as Black Lives Matter riots provide a great opportunity for President Trump to push law and order.

“All the major battleground states, except for Michigan, seem to be trending tighter and tighter,” Mr Horowitz told Sky News host Paul Murray.

“And Frankly, the riots that happened in Philadelphia over the last couple of days … this could not have been scripted better for the president.

“He should be pointing to this as an example of ‘hey, Pennsylvania, you need to be looking to me not just because Biden wants to get rid of all fracking, all fossil fuels’ … but also because this law and order thing plays really well in those rural and suburb areas of Pennsylvania.

“He could not have scripted this better, it’s getting really really tight.”

video_title: Nebraska Trump rally turn out of  29,000 people was a 'wake-up moment for the media'
video_description:
Sky News US political commentator Joe Hockey says when 29,000 people turned up for a Trump rally in Nebraska the other day, it was a wake-up moment for the media.
 
“It is extraordinary, it’s almost like a cult movement and he’s like a cult leader and people are coming out in vast numbers,” Mr Hockey said. 

Mr Hockey said Trump went to five cities across the country on Sunday, and people in Florida were queued up waiting for his arrival from 7am right through until beyond 11:30pm. 

“It is building a momentum, there’s no doubt about that,” he said.

“He is hungry and it shows. He really wants people votes and that’s given him momentum in the last 48 hours.

“It’s really hard to read the impact of that momentum on the electoral votes.”

Joe Biden: "They're gonna put y'all back in chains..."

"Americans use firearms to defend themselves between 500,000 and two million times every year. God forbid that my mother is ever faced with a scenario where she has to stop a threat to her life. But if she is, I hope politicians protected by professional armed security didn't strip her of the right to use the firearm she can handle most competently." – Amy Swearer
